Defendant Kerry Antonio Taper in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Defendant Kerry Antonio Taper in custody.  
Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

COUNT 2:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate that the behavior in this incident constituted resisting.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  

COUNT 1:  Pursuant to plea negotiations the Court orders Count 1 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 2.

Statements made as to sentencing by the state, defense, and defendant.

The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, Straight time with credit for 61 DAYS time served.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 12 MONTHS with the following conditions:

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens;
*No contact with victim Jeannie W.;
*Submit to agent letter of apology- to be forwarded to the victim;
*Participate in Anger management;
*Complete 15 hours of community service;
*Make an earnest effort towards full time employment;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  

The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  Filed, Pretrial Incarceration Credit and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
